{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1014,"text":"You may be wondering"},{"time":2230,"text":"why a marine biologist from Oceana"},{"time":4064,"text":"would come here today to talk to you"},{"time":5904,"text":"about world hunger."},{"time":7140,"text":"I'm here today because"},{"time":9291,"text":"saving the oceans is more than an ecological desire."},{"time":12526,"text":"It's more than a thing we're doing"},{"time":14670,"text":"because we want to create jobs for fishermen"},{"time":16468,"text":"or preserve fishermen's jobs."},{"time":18552,"text":"It's more than an economic pursuit."},{"time":21900,"text":"Saving the oceans can feed the world."},{"time":24512,"text":"Let me show you how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26338,"text":"As you know, there are already"},{"time":28140,"text":"more than a billion hungry people on this planet."},{"time":30766,"text":"We're expecting that problem to get worse"},{"time":33116,"text":"as world population grows to nine billion"},{"time":35546,"text":"or 10 billion by midcentury,"},{"time":37410,"text":"and we can expect to have greater pressure"},{"time":40388,"text":"on our food resources."},{"time":42246,"text":"And this is a big concern,"},{"time":43290,"text":"especially considering where we are now."},{"time":45956,"text":"Now we know that our arable land per capita"},{"time":48668,"text":"is already on the decline"},{"time":50096,"text":"in both developed and developing countries."},{"time":52805,"text":"We know that we're headed for climate change,"},{"time":55460,"text":"which is going to change rainfall patterns,"},{"time":57876,"text":"making some areas drier, as you can see in orange,"},{"time":61186,"text":"and others wetter, in blue,"},{"time":63497,"text":"causing droughts in our breadbaskets,"},{"time":65240,"text":"in places like the Midwest and Central Europe,"},{"time":67090,"text":"and floods in others."},{"time":68372,"text":"It's going to make it harder for the land"},{"time":70134,"text":"to help us solve the hunger problem."},{"time":72690,"text":"And that's why the oceans need\nto be their most abundant,"},{"time":75154,"text":"so that the oceans can provide us"},{"time":76728,"text":"as much food as possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79321,"text":"And that's something the oceans have been doing"},{"time":80968,"text":"for us for a long time."},{"time":83610,"text":"As far back as we can go, we've seen an increase"},{"time":86290,"text":"in the amount of food we've been able to harvest"},{"time":88233,"text":"from our oceans."},{"time":89897,"text":"It just seemed like it was continuing to increase,"},{"time":92385,"text":"until about 1980,"},{"time":93789,"text":"when we started to see a decline."},{"time":96585,"text":"You've heard of peak oil."},{"time":98183,"text":"Maybe this is peak fish."},{"time":100170,"text":"I hope not. I'm going to come back to that."},{"time":101970,"text":"But you can see about an 18-percent decline"},{"time":104473,"text":"in the amount of fish we've gotten in our world catch"},{"time":107425,"text":"since 1980."},{"time":108780,"text":"And this is a big problem. It's continuing."},{"time":111040,"text":"This red line is continuing to go down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113397,"text":"But we know how to turn it around,"},{"time":115493,"text":"and that's what I'm going to talk about today."},{"time":117183,"text":"We know how to turn that curve back upwards."},{"time":119583,"text":"This doesn't have to be peak fish."},{"time":122030,"text":"If we do a few simple things in targeted places,"},{"time":125219,"text":"we can bring our fisheries back and use them"},{"time":127702,"text":"to feed people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129966,"text":"First we want to know where the fish are,"},{"time":131886,"text":"so let's look where the fish are."},{"time":133457,"text":"It turns out the fish, conveniently,"},{"time":135351,"text":"are located for the most part"},{"time":137567,"text":"in our coastal areas of the countries,"},{"time":139630,"text":"in coastal zones,"},{"time":140935,"text":"and these are areas that national jurisdictions"},{"time":143339,"text":"have control over,"},{"time":144721,"text":"and they can manage their fisheries"},{"time":146545,"text":"in these coastal areas."},{"time":148204,"text":"Coastal countries tend to have jurisdictions"},{"time":150462,"text":"that go out about 200 nautical miles,"},{"time":153070,"text":"in areas that are called exclusive economic zones,"},{"time":156441,"text":"and this is a good thing that they can control"},{"time":158434,"text":"their fisheries in these areas,"},{"time":159595,"text":"because the high seas,"},{"time":161111,"text":"which are the darker areas on this map,"},{"time":163404,"text":"the high seas, it's a lot harder to control things,"},{"time":165603,"text":"because it has to be done internationally."},{"time":167692,"text":"You get into international agreements,"},{"time":169559,"text":"and if any of you are tracking\nthe climate change agreement,"},{"time":171807,"text":"you know this can be a very slow,"},{"time":173519,"text":"frustrating, tedious process."},{"time":175501,"text":"And so controlling things nationally"},{"time":177223,"text":"is a great thing to be able to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179997,"text":"How many fish are actually in these coastal areas"},{"time":182194,"text":"compared to the high seas?"},{"time":183771,"text":"Well, you can see here about"},{"time":185281,"text":"seven times as many fish in the coastal areas"},{"time":188364,"text":"than there are in the high seas,"},{"time":189951,"text":"so this is a perfect place for us to be focusing,"},{"time":192167,"text":"because we can actually get a lot done."},{"time":194311,"text":"We can restore a lot of our fisheries"},{"time":196701,"text":"if we focus in these coastal areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198895,"text":"But how many of these countries\ndo we have to work in?"},{"time":201919,"text":"There's something like 80 coastal countries."},{"time":203521,"text":"Do we have to fix fisheries management"},{"time":205507,"text":"in all of those countries?"},{"time":206910,"text":"So we asked ourselves, how many countries"},{"time":209032,"text":"do we need to focus on,"},{"time":210439,"text":"keeping in mind that the European Union"},{"time":212301,"text":"conveniently manages its fisheries"},{"time":213870,"text":"through a common fisheries policy?"},{"time":216237,"text":"So if we got good fisheries management"},{"time":218529,"text":"in the European Union and,\nsay, nine other countries,"},{"time":221794,"text":"how much of our fisheries would we be covering?"},{"time":223883,"text":"Turns out, European Union plus nine countries"},{"time":226940,"text":"covers about two thirds of the world's fish catch."},{"time":230054,"text":"If we took it up to 24 countries\nplus the European Union,"},{"time":233333,"text":"we would up to 90 percent,"},{"time":235055,"text":"almost all of the world's fish catch."},{"time":238265,"text":"So we think we can work in\na limited number of places"},{"time":241193,"text":"to make the fisheries come back."},{"time":242885,"text":"But what do we have to do in these places?"},{"time":245497,"text":"Well, based on our work in the United States"},{"time":247292,"text":"and elsewhere, we know that there are"},{"time":248880,"text":"three key things we have to do"},{"time":250721,"text":"to bring fisheries back, and they are:"},{"time":253427,"text":"We need to set quotas or limits"},{"time":255373,"text":"on how much we take;"},{"time":257480,"text":"we need to reduce bycatch, which is the accidental"},{"time":260273,"text":"catching and killing of fish that we're not targeting,"},{"time":262609,"text":"and it's very wasteful;"},{"time":264459,"text":"and three, we need to protect habitats,"},{"time":267123,"text":"the nursery areas, the spawning areas"},{"time":269240,"text":"that these fish need to grow\nand reproduce successfully"},{"time":271810,"text":"so that they can rebuild their populations."},{"time":273660,"text":"If we do those three things, we \nknow the fisheries will come back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277422,"text":"How do we know?"},{"time":278770,"text":"We know because we've seen it happening"},{"time":280785,"text":"in a lot of different places."},{"time":282213,"text":"This is a slide that shows"},{"time":283654,"text":"the herring population in Norway"},{"time":285852,"text":"that was crashing since the 1950s."},{"time":288175,"text":"It was coming down, and when Norway set limits,"},{"time":290326,"text":"or quotas, on its fishery, what happens?"},{"time":293244,"text":"The fishery comes back."},{"time":295110,"text":"This is another example, also\nhappens to be from Norway,"},{"time":298010,"text":"of the Norwegian Arctic cod."},{"time":300468,"text":"Same deal. The fishery is crashing."},{"time":302524,"text":"They set limits on discards."},{"time":304484,"text":"Discards are these fish they weren't targeting"},{"time":306598,"text":"and they get thrown overboard wastefully."},{"time":309200,"text":"When they set the discard limit,"},{"time":310812,"text":"the fishery came back."},{"time":312868,"text":"And it's not just in Norway."},{"time":314135,"text":"We've seen this happening in countries"},{"time":316094,"text":"all around the world, time and time again."},{"time":319153,"text":"When these countries step in and they"},{"time":320686,"text":"put in sustainable fisheries management policies,"},{"time":323820,"text":"the fisheries, which are always crashing, it seems,"},{"time":326636,"text":"are starting to come back."},{"time":328574,"text":"So there's a lot of promise here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330432,"text":"What does this mean for the world fish catch?"},{"time":332124,"text":"This means that if we take that fishery catch"},{"time":334460,"text":"that's on the decline"},{"time":335490,"text":"and we could turn it upwards, we could increase it"},{"time":337878,"text":"up to 100 million metric tons per year."},{"time":341416,"text":"So we didn't have peak fish yet."},{"time":343389,"text":"We still have an opportunity"},{"time":344916,"text":"to not only bring the fish back"},{"time":346217,"text":"but to actually get more fish"},{"time":347920,"text":"that can feed more people"},{"time":349371,"text":"than we currently are now."},{"time":350873,"text":"How many more? Right about now,"},{"time":352979,"text":"we can feed about 450 million people"},{"time":355860,"text":"a fish meal a day"},{"time":356834,"text":"based on the current world fish catch,"},{"time":359084,"text":"which, of course, you know is going down,"},{"time":361548,"text":"so that number will go down over time"},{"time":363203,"text":"if we don't fix it,"},{"time":364806,"text":"but if we put fishery management practices"},{"time":367216,"text":"like the ones I've described in place"},{"time":369780,"text":"in 10 to 25 countries,"},{"time":371885,"text":"we could bring that number up"},{"time":373364,"text":"and feed as many as 700 million people a year"},{"time":376918,"text":"a healthy fish meal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378466,"text":"We should obviously do this just because"},{"time":380008,"text":"it's a good thing to deal with the hunger problem,"},{"time":383000,"text":"but it's also cost-effective."},{"time":384177,"text":"It turns out fish is the most cost-effective protein"},{"time":388524,"text":"on the planet."},{"time":389900,"text":"If you look at how much fish protein you get"},{"time":392030,"text":"per dollar invested"},{"time":393030,"text":"compared to all of the other animal proteins,"},{"time":395762,"text":"obviously, fish is a good business decision."},{"time":398692,"text":"It also doesn't need a lot of land,"},{"time":400292,"text":"something that's in short supply,"},{"time":401758,"text":"compared to other protein sources."},{"time":405276,"text":"And it doesn't need a lot of fresh water."},{"time":407907,"text":"It uses a lot less fresh water than,"},{"time":409979,"text":"for example, cattle,"},{"time":411020,"text":"where you have to irrigate a field"},{"time":413174,"text":"so that you can grow the food to graze the cattle."},{"time":416317,"text":"It also has a very low carbon footprint."},{"time":418436,"text":"It has a little bit of a carbon footprint"},{"time":420316,"text":"because we do have to get out and catch the fish."},{"time":422315,"text":"It takes a little bit of fuel,"},{"time":423810,"text":"but as you know, agriculture\ncan have a carbon footprint,"},{"time":426032,"text":"and fish has a much smaller one,"},{"time":427586,"text":"so it's less polluting."},{"time":429360,"text":"It's already a big part of our diet,"},{"time":431741,"text":"but it can be a bigger part of our diet,"},{"time":433830,"text":"which is a good thing, because we know"},{"time":435561,"text":"that it's healthy for us."},{"time":437186,"text":"It can reduce our risks of cancer,"},{"time":439511,"text":"heart disease and obesity."},{"time":441400,"text":"In fact, our CEO Andy Sharpless,"},{"time":443371,"text":"who is the originator of this concept, actually,"},{"time":445960,"text":"he likes to say fish is the perfect protein."},{"time":449880,"text":"Andy also talks about the fact that"},{"time":452130,"text":"our ocean conservation movement really grew"},{"time":454636,"text":"out of the land conservation movement,"},{"time":456868,"text":"and in land conservation,"},{"time":458360,"text":"we have this problem where biodiversity"},{"time":461424,"text":"is at war with food production."},{"time":464424,"text":"You have to cut down the biodiverse forest"},{"time":467215,"text":"if you want to get the field"},{"time":469108,"text":"to grow the corn to feed people with,"},{"time":471338,"text":"and so there's a constant push-pull there."},{"time":473180,"text":"There's a constant tough decision"},{"time":474728,"text":"that has to be made between"},{"time":476567,"text":"two very important things:"},{"time":478588,"text":"maintaining biodiversity and feeding people."},{"time":481681,"text":"But in the oceans, we don't have that war."},{"time":483981,"text":"In the oceans, biodiversity is not at war"},{"time":486538,"text":"with abundance."},{"time":487700,"text":"In fact, they're aligned."},{"time":489805,"text":"When we do things that produce biodiversity,"},{"time":492978,"text":"we actually get more abundance,"},{"time":495030,"text":"and that's important so that we can feed people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498846,"text":"Now, there's a catch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501576,"text":"Didn't anyone get that? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504121,"text":"Illegal fishing."},{"time":506164,"text":"Illegal fishing undermines the type of"},{"time":507730,"text":"sustainable fisheries management I'm talking about."},{"time":509980,"text":"It can be when you catch fish using gears"},{"time":512460,"text":"that have been prohibited,"},{"time":513489,"text":"when you fish in places where\nyou're not supposed to fish,"},{"time":516140,"text":"you catch fish that are the wrong\nsize or the wrong species."},{"time":519378,"text":"Illegal fishing cheats the consumer"},{"time":521343,"text":"and it also cheats honest fishermen,"},{"time":523550,"text":"and it needs to stop."},{"time":524710,"text":"The way illegal fish get into our \nmarket is through seafood fraud."},{"time":527787,"text":"You might have heard about this."},{"time":529236,"text":"It's when fish are labeled as something they're not."},{"time":532420,"text":"Think about the last time you had fish."},{"time":533955,"text":"What were you eating?"},{"time":534745,"text":"Are you sure that's what it was?"},{"time":536516,"text":"Because we tested 1,300 different fish samples"},{"time":539240,"text":"and about a third of them"},{"time":540482,"text":"were not what they were labeled to be."},{"time":542220,"text":"Snappers, nine out of 10\nsnappers were not snapper."},{"time":544960,"text":"Fifty-nine percent of the tuna we tested"},{"time":547180,"text":"was mislabeled."},{"time":549150,"text":"And red snapper, we tested 120 samples,"},{"time":551778,"text":"and only seven of them were really red snapper,"},{"time":553694,"text":"so good luck finding a red snapper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557238,"text":"Seafood has a really complex supply chain,"},{"time":559466,"text":"and at every step in this supply chain,"},{"time":561762,"text":"there's an opportunity for seafood fraud,"},{"time":563952,"text":"unless we have traceability."},{"time":566080,"text":"Traceability is a way where the seafood industry"},{"time":568799,"text":"can track the seafood from the boat to the plate"},{"time":571096,"text":"to make sure that the consumer can then find out"},{"time":573627,"text":"where their seafood came from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575274,"text":"This is a really important thing."},{"time":577030,"text":"It's being done by some in\nthe industry, but not enough,"},{"time":579598,"text":"so we're pushing a law in Congress"},{"time":580945,"text":"called the SAFE Seafood Act,"},{"time":582351,"text":"and I'm very excited today to announce the release"},{"time":584990,"text":"of a chef's petition, where 450 chefs"},{"time":587634,"text":"have signed a petition calling on Congress"},{"time":590306,"text":"to support the SAFE Seafood Act."},{"time":592508,"text":"It has a lot of celebrity chefs you may know --"},{"time":594336,"text":"Anthony Bourdain, Mario Batali,"},{"time":597540,"text":"Barton Seaver and others —"},{"time":599216,"text":"and they've signed it because they believe"},{"time":600970,"text":"that people have a right to know"},{"time":602298,"text":"about what they're eating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604673,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":610464,"text":"Fishermen like it too, so there's a good chance"},{"time":612420,"text":"we can get the kind of support we need"},{"time":614020,"text":"to get this bill through,"},{"time":614954,"text":"and it comes at a critical time,"},{"time":616478,"text":"because this is the way we stop seafood fraud,"},{"time":618584,"text":"this is the way we curb illegal fishing,"},{"time":620650,"text":"and this is the way we make sure"},{"time":622522,"text":"that quotas, habitat protection,"},{"time":624226,"text":"and bycatch reductions can do the jobs"},{"time":626106,"text":"they can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627283,"text":"We know that we can manage\nour fisheries sustainably."},{"time":630459,"text":"We know that we can produce"},{"time":632101,"text":"healthy meals for hundreds of millions of people"},{"time":635870,"text":"that don't use the land, that don't use much water,"},{"time":638115,"text":"have a low carbon footprint,"},{"time":639300,"text":"and are cost-effective."},{"time":641102,"text":"We know that saving the oceans"},{"time":643090,"text":"can feed the world,"},{"time":644673,"text":"and we need to start now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647060,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649817,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}